1
00:00:03,498 --> 00:00:07,650
Сreation is a secondary function
performed

2
00:00:07,650 --> 00:00:10,969
by a part of a part of a part
of His expansion

3
00:00:10,969 --> 00:00:12,869
with His eyes half-closed.

4
00:00:13,008 --> 00:00:15,668
[With My Eyes Closed]

5
00:00:16,110 --> 00:00:17,625
Like we say in this world,

6
00:00:17,625 --> 00:00:19,323
when people think 
they are good at something,

7
00:00:19,323 --> 00:00:21,644
they say, “I can do that 
with my eyes closed.”

8
00:00:21,644 --> 00:00:23,756
“Yes, you can do that
with your eyes closed.”

9
00:00:23,756 --> 00:00:25,823
But it’s generally an expression,

10
00:00:25,823 --> 00:00:28,142
“I can do this with my eyes closed.”

11
00:00:28,142 --> 00:00:31,916
You can do those kinds of things
or maybe not.

12
00:00:31,916 --> 00:00:35,346
Mahāviṣṇu generates innumerable Universes

13
00:00:35,346 --> 00:00:39,404
out of His pores 
with His eyes half-closed,

14
00:00:39,773 --> 00:00:44,329
half-asleep, 
He is lying in yoga-nidrā

15
00:00:44,329 --> 00:00:48,230
with His eyes half-closed, 
half-asleep

16
00:00:48,230 --> 00:00:52,229
and His glance
is personified as Śambhu Śiva,

17
00:00:52,229 --> 00:00:54,087
full of the sum total of jīvas

18
00:00:54,087 --> 00:00:57,047
and they are impregnated
in the material nature. 

19
00:00:57,047 --> 00:01:00,216
All He is doing is [exhales]:

20
00:01:00,982 --> 00:01:03,630
His outward going breath

21
00:01:03,630 --> 00:01:07,313
hundred and fifty trillion years,

22
00:01:07,672 --> 00:01:09,628
innumerable Universes appear,

23
00:01:09,628 --> 00:01:11,800
He can do it with His eyes closed,

24
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:14,716
while Kṛṣṇa’s playing

25
00:01:14,716 --> 00:01:20,073
with the gopas and gopīs in Vṛndāvan.

26
00:01:20,073 --> 00:01:22,521
That’s Beauty Over Power.

27
00:01:22,521 --> 00:01:25,281
There are many examples of
Beauty Over Power.

28
00:01:25,281 --> 00:01:31,181
Kṛṣṇa over Rāmachandra,
Kṛṣṇa over Viṣṇu.

29
00:01:31,842 --> 00:01:36,742
The ultimate conception
of the ultimate reality is beauty.

30
00:01:36,742 --> 00:01:37,997
And as Guru Mahārāj says,

31
00:01:37,997 --> 00:01:41,622
“Beauty is the ultimate controlling principle.”

32
00:01:41,622 --> 00:01:47,146
So, Mahāviṣṇu steals that brāhmaṇ’s boy,

33
00:01:47,146 --> 00:01:50,831
why? We find out in the Bhāgavatam,

34
00:01:52,010 --> 00:01:56,542
He wants to see the Beauty of Kṛṣṇa.

35
00:01:56,542 --> 00:01:58,112
How to get Kṛṣṇa to come?

36
00:01:58,112 --> 00:02:01,795
He stole the boy and
He is keeping him there

37
00:02:01,795 --> 00:02:03,962
we think such a cruel thing to do,

38
00:02:03,962 --> 00:02:06,151
and Kṛṣṇa and Arjuna go through

39
00:02:06,151 --> 00:02:08,454
all the layers of the Universe 
and then Mahāviṣṇu says,

40
00:02:08,454 --> 00:02:12,155
“I just wanted to see
Your beauty, my Lord.”

41
00:02:12,155 --> 00:02:15,316
Should we think that
Viṣṇu is not beautiful?

42
00:02:15,316 --> 00:02:18,042
Inconceivably beautiful.

43
00:02:18,042 --> 00:02:22,907
But was the śloka of the day? 

44
00:02:22,907 --> 00:02:26,507
sarvādbhuta-chamatkāra-
līlā-kallola-vāridhiḥ

45
00:02:26,507 --> 00:02:30,805
atulya-madhura-prema-
maṇḍita-priya-maṇḍalaḥ

46
00:02:30,805 --> 00:02:36,843
trijagan-mānasākarṣi-
muralī-kala-kūjitaḥ
(Cc: Madhya, 23.82-83)

47
00:02:36,843 --> 00:02:40,699
Kūjitaḥ: it sounds very beautiful,

48
00:02:40,699 --> 00:02:43,746
muralī—Kṛṣṇa’s flute,

49
00:02:43,746 --> 00:02:47,332
muralī-kala-kūjitaḥ

50
00:02:50,685 --> 00:02:54,895
asamānordhva-rūpa-śrī:

51
00:02:55,026 --> 00:02:57,580
no one equals His beauty,

52
00:02:57,580 --> 00:03:01,495
not Viṣṇu, not Rāma, 
not Dvārakā-Kṛṣṇa.

53
00:03:02,872 --> 00:03:06,919
Dvārakā-Kṛṣṇa sees the picture and says,

54
00:03:06,919 --> 00:03:11,769
“I was so beautiful 
when I was younger in Vṛndāvan.”

55
00:03:11,769 --> 00:03:14,677
Like in this world.

56
00:03:14,677 --> 00:03:18,329
My cousin, who is my age,

57
00:03:18,329 --> 00:03:19,182
she told my mom

58
00:03:19,182 --> 00:03:20,810
now I won’t say her age,

59
00:03:20,810 --> 00:03:23,512
because somehow over the years

60
00:03:23,512 --> 00:03:25,521
there are like ten years separating us,

61
00:03:25,521 --> 00:03:29,284
even though we we’re born 
in the same year.

62
00:03:31,834 --> 00:03:35,175
Anyway, and my mom is ninety-three,

63
00:03:35,175 --> 00:03:37,898
she doesn’t mind me saying that.

64
00:03:38,779 --> 00:03:40,936
My cousin said to her,

65
00:03:40,936 --> 00:03:45,854
“Aunt Rose, let’s look at some pictures 
when we used to look good,

66
00:03:45,854 --> 00:03:48,852
when we used to be beautiful.”

67
00:03:48,852 --> 00:03:53,032
So, Kṛṣṇa also has a version of that,

68
00:03:53,032 --> 00:03:55,744
He’s saying,
“Oh, I was so beautiful in Vṛndāvan,

69
00:03:55,744 --> 00:03:58,026
now these days …”

70
00:03:58,416 --> 00:04:01,722
Maybe [He] put on 
a little weight in Dvārakā,

71
00:04:01,722 --> 00:04:03,926
it’s hard to say.

72
00:04:05,205 --> 00:04:08,639
Or He sees His own Beauty

73
00:04:08,639 --> 00:04:11,056
in a jewelled column and says,

74
00:04:11,056 --> 00:04:12,509
“Who is so beautiful

75
00:04:12,509 --> 00:04:13,809
that now I am starting to feel

76
00:04:13,809 --> 00:04:16,262
the same feelings as Rādhikā?”

77
00:04:18,536 --> 00:04:24,270
So, even Kṛṣṇa is enamoured
by His own beauty,

78
00:04:24,270 --> 00:04:27,502
asamānordhva-rūpa-śrī

79
00:04:27,530 --> 00:04:27,530
The rūpa means form

80
00:04:30,279 --> 00:04:34,279
Rūpa śrī, śrī rūpa. 

